Senate State and Local Government 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1654
Briggs
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1654* House Bill No. 1648
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting instead:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 56, Chapter 7, Part 31, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
A non-governmental entity receiving in-kind funding from the state or a political
subdivision of the state pursuant to § 317 or § 318 of the Public Health Service Act (42
U.S.C. §§ 247b and 247c), is eligible to qualify as a 340B entity, as defined in § 56-7-
3119, only if the entity is also a recipient of one (1) or more state or federal grant awards
that are subject to audit, reporting, and oversight requirements under state and federal
law. The comptroller of the treasury and any state agency or political subdivision
providing in-kind funding are authorized to verify eligibility and enforce compliance with
this section.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect November 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
